text: Hey traders, Captain Jim here. I just want to talk to you real quick about where we are in the market.
Now we are in a very positive environment right now and certain stocks like Apple were able to
make some decent highs today which held the market up and allowed a lot of beaten down stocks to
come up. You look at the snaps, you look at the Roku's out there, PayPal's all able to come up

I do still want you to think about these moves that are made. You see these giant moves here,
see another giant move here, and you see another giant move right here. Now even though we've
flipped too positive in the market, overall looks like it's going to continue to push up.
You have to see how big this move really is in here. How important it is to recognize where these
moves are and what does that mean for where we are today. Now there is a volatility level above here
and there is on the spy as well. I'm going to show you the spy right now. I'm going to talk
to you about this and the reason I'm talking to you about this is because initially if you look at
the spy here, this looks like it's going to make one more move. You got that one, two, and this is
forming your number three push up that everyone is expecting. I don't know if that happens exactly
at this moment right now or if it continues to trail down and then makes that last move. My one
concern though is this. Even though we're in a positive gamut environment,
you'll hear traders say things like, well we kept going up but I lost money while we were going up
and oftentimes that is because they are not buying at the right moments in the market
even though we're going up. You'll see these FOMO buyers up in here. They'll get trapped,
they'll pull it back down a little bit and then we'll move forward. When we make that move forward,
how that fuels the market is, bulls being trapped knowing that we're in positive gamma,
we'll then re-enter with more money to get us to untrap them over here. As we move forward
right now, this looks like to me a day where I'm not going to take a trade. This is too risky for
me and I really want to see it come down a little bit more before I take that next trade. Let's just
say I get left behind in the dust. Let's say it's like, hey Captain Jim, you missed the top over here.
Well, I'm still going to be looking at that point for these all-time highs and a sell-down
for me to grab the next run-up but I just need you guys to understand where we are right now.
It's starting to get riskier and riskier as the day moves on. Hope all is well out there
and I'm not buying any, I'm not going short here right now because I know the market can get
crazier rational. I know the market can hit all-time highs today, definitely into tomorrow but this,
just this basing pattern right here that I'm seeing is letting me to believe that it's not
done basing, that we might come down a little bit. It could be today, it could be into tomorrow
and then a rip higher. So just be aware of that as we move forward today.
